        [
          "Nosferatu faking a Toreador",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Rachel Judd"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You always thought you were too good for government work, but when a lucrative position opened up at the San Antonio DWP, you took it. You didn't think government jobs were so cushy, but yours was. Then the market crashed, and you *needed* a job. So you stayed, resenting your circumstances. It might have stopped there, but then you got engaged. You simply could not shut up about your fiancee and what beautiful children you'd make together. Distracted by wedding planning, your work suffered. Long story short, you ended up becoming a spite Embrace - your sire bequeathing you the Blood as a punishment for your vanity and self-absorption. Only, the Embrace didn't go the way your sire thought it would be. Your body is a mangled mess of sagging skin, unsightly body hair, taloned feet and hands... but your face remains untouched. You tried to fit in with the other Nosferatu, but you simply couldn't put up with their monstrousness. So, as soon as you could, you ran away and passed yourself off as a Caitiff in Dallas. There, you met Veronique, a Toreador neonate who had earned the ire of her own sire. You befriended her, seduced her, convinced her to drink your blood. Once you had utterly won her devotion, you convinced her to claim you as her childe. Which, of course, she did. You promptly drank Veronique dry and moved to San Francisco with the sad tale of your sire's death at the hands of the Sabbat. You fit in very well, pretending to be overtly religious to explain why you kept so well-covered. A little odd, as your chosen art form is very visceral - you practice tattooing, body modification and piercing; helping others show off their body while you must always keep yours hidden. But then the NPM took over San Francisco, and so you've fled to LA, looking for a new home among the Toreador. NOTE: You must cover up your hair, neck, hands, etc. If anyone ever sees a part of your body that is not your face, they will know you are not not Toreador. And Veronique isn't gone. Some part of her remained when you diablerized her, and she lingers in your head, mocking you constantly for being a fake Toreador."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Mee-ku the Unclean (real), Veronique St. Croix (fake)",
          "Reference: (If any)",
